title: Film criticism and caricatures, 1943-53 (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Barnes & Noble Books | 1976 | Pdf | Eng | ISBN 0064977668 | 196 p | 36 MB

Richard Winnington was News Chronicle film critic from 1943 until his death in
1953 momentous period in cinema history which saw the rise of French, Italian and British cinema simultaneously with the late heyday of Hollywood.

Winnington's enthusiasms, at preview after preview, lit on a major proportion of
what are now generally agreed to be the most important films of the period. At the same time, - his column reminds today's cinema-lover of some forgotten films of outstanding quality
